  "title": "Monitoring Adult Populations of Maruca testulalis  (Geyer) with Light Traps at Patancheru and Hisarin India",
  "abstract": "Maruca  testulalis  (Geyer)  is  the  most  damaging  insect pest of pigeonpea in some areas of Asia and Africa. The larvae  of  this  insect  web  the  leaves  and  terminal  buds together, and  feed and pupate inside  this web. Attacks  by this  insect  can  last  up  to  the podding  stage.",
